**`Partial<T>`**: `{ [K in keyof T]?: T[K] }` — tất cả fields thành optional. Tuyệt vời cho update operations khi chỉ gửi changed fields.

**`Required<T>`**: Ngược lại với `Partial` — biến tất cả optional fields thành required.

**`Pick<T, K>`**: Tạo type với chỉ các keys được chỉ định từ T. Dùng để select fields cho một view cụ thể.

**`Omit<T, K>`**: Tạo type loại trừ các keys được chỉ định. Dùng để ẩn internal fields.

**`Record<K, V>`**: `{ [key in K]: V }` — tạo mapped type. Dùng cho dictionaries/maps.

**Ví dụ thực tế — Single source of truth**:
```ts
// Entity gốc
interface User {
  id: string;
  email: string;
  password: string;
  name: string;
  createdAt: Date;
  role: 'admin' | 'user';
}

// Derive các DTOs
type CreateUserDto = Omit<User, 'id' | 'createdAt'>;
type UpdateUserDto = Partial<Omit<User, 'id' | 'createdAt'>>;
type UserResponse = Omit<User, 'password'>;
type UserSummary = Pick<User, 'id' | 'name' | 'email'>;
```

**Lợi ích**:
- Thay đổi `User` tự động update tất cả derived types
- Không duplicate field definitions
- Type-safe API contracts

**Declaration merging**: TypeScript merge nhiều declarations cùng tên trong cùng scope:
- **Interface merging**: Hai interfaces cùng tên merge members
- **Namespace merging**: Namespaces merge với classes, functions, hoặc enums
- **Module augmentation**: Mở rộng module declarations từ external packages

**Interface merging**:
```ts
interface User { name: string; }
interface User { email: string; }
// Kết quả: interface User { name: string; email: string; }
```

**Module augmentation** — Mở rộng Express Request:
```ts
// types/express.d.ts
import { User } from '../models/user';

declare module 'express-serve-static-core' {
  interface Request {
    user?: User;
    sessionId: string;
  }
}
```

**Khi dùng**:
- Thêm custom properties vào library objects (Express req, Fastify, etc.)
- Fix incorrect library types trong khi chờ PR merge
- Extend global types (Window, NodeJS.ProcessEnv)

**Risks**:
- **Drift**: Library update có thể conflict với augmentation
- **Hidden dependencies**: Team members không biết type được augmented
- **Over-augmentation**: Thêm quá nhiều có thể gây confusing

**Best practices**:
- Đặt augmentations trong folder `types/` riêng
- Comment rõ tại sao cần augmentation
- Prefer wrapping over augmenting khi có thể

**Cấu trúc**: Mỗi variant có shared property với unique literal type:
```ts
type Result<T> =
  | { status: 'success'; data: T }
  | { status: 'error'; error: Error }
  | { status: 'loading' };
```

**Narrowing**: `switch`/`if` trên discriminant thu hẹp type:
```ts
function handle(result: Result<User>) {
  switch (result.status) {
    case 'success': return result.data; // TS biết data exists
    case 'error': throw result.error;   // TS biết error exists
    case 'loading': return null;
  }
}
```

**Exhaustive checking** — Bắt missing cases:
```ts
function assertNever(x: never): never {
  throw new Error(`Unexpected: ${x}`);
}

switch (result.status) {
  case 'success': ...
  case 'error': ...
  // Nếu thêm 'loading' mà quên handle,
  // default case sẽ compile error
  default: assertNever(result);
}
```

**Tại sao hơn class hierarchies**:
- **Serializable**: Plain objects, easy JSON serialize/deserialize
- **Pattern matching**: Switch statements clear hơn instanceof checks
- **Closed set**: Compiler biết tất cả variants — class hierarchies có thể extended bởi anyone
- **Functional style**: Không cần methods, chỉ data và functions xử lý chúng

**Use cases**:
- API response states (loading/success/error)
- Redux/reducer actions
- Form validation results
- State machine states

**Generics basics**: Cho phép functions/classes hoạt động với nhiều types trong khi maintain type safety. Thay vì `any`, type variable `T` preserve specific types.

**Constraints** (`extends`): Restrict types `T` có thể là. `T extends { id: string }` nghĩa là T phải có ít nhất `id` property kiểu `string`.

**Implementing `keyBy`**:
```ts
function keyBy<T extends { id: PropertyKey }>(
  items: T[]
): Map<T['id'], T> {
  const map = new Map<T['id'], T>();
  for (const item of items) {
    map.set(item.id, item);
  }
  return map;
}

// Usage
interface User { id: string; name: string; }
const users: User[] = [{ id: '1', name: 'Alice' }];
const userMap = keyBy(users); // Map<string, User>
```

**Flexible key**:
```ts
function keyBy<T, K extends keyof T>(
  items: T[],
  key: K
): Map<T[K], T> {
  const map = new Map<T[K], T>();
  for (const item of items) {
    map.set(item[key], item);
  }
  return map;
}

keyBy(users, 'id');   // Map<string, User>
keyBy(users, 'name'); // Map<string, User>
```

**Common patterns**:
- `T extends unknown[]` — array constraint
- `T extends (...args: any[]) => any` — function constraint
- `T extends new (...args: any[]) => any` — constructor constraint

**Mapped types**: Transform mỗi property của existing type:
```ts
type Readonly<T> = { readonly [K in keyof T]: T[K] };
type Optional<T> = { [K in keyof T]?: T[K] };
```

**Template literal types**: String manipulation at type level:
```ts
type EventName = 'click' | 'focus' | 'blur';
type HandlerName = `on${Capitalize<EventName>}`;
// 'onClick' | 'onFocus' | 'onBlur'
```

**Building type-safe event emitter**:
```ts
type Events = {
  click: { x: number; y: number };
  focus: { target: HTMLElement };
  submit: { data: FormData };
};

type EventHandlers<E> = {
  [K in keyof E as `on${Capitalize<string & K>}`]: (payload: E[K]) => void;
};

type MyHandlers = EventHandlers<Events>;
// {
//   onClick: (payload: { x: number; y: number }) => void;
//   onFocus: (payload: { target: HTMLElement }) => void;
//   onSubmit: (payload: { data: FormData }) => void;
// }
```

**Key remapping với `as`**: Cho phép transform key names trong mapped types.

**Advanced example** — Getters và Setters:
```ts
type Accessors<T> = {
  [K in keyof T as `get${Capitalize<string & K>}`]: () => T[K];
} & {
  [K in keyof T as `set${Capitalize<string & K>}`]: (value: T[K]) => void;
};
```

**Component re-renders khi**:
1. State thay đổi (`useState`, `useReducer`)
2. Props thay đổi
3. Parent re-renders (tất cả children re-render by default)
4. Context value thay đổi
5. Custom hook state changes

**Ngăn unnecessary renders**:

**1. React.memo** cho function components:
```tsx
const ExpensiveList = React.memo(({ items }) => {
  return items.map(item => <Item key={item.id} {...item} />);
});
// Chỉ re-render khi items thay đổi
```

**2. useMemo** cho expensive computations:
```tsx
const sortedItems = useMemo(() => {
  return items.sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));
}, [items]);
```

**3. useCallback** cho stable function references:
```tsx
const handleClick = useCallback((id) => {
  deleteItem(id);
}, [deleteItem]);
```

**4. Lift state up correctly**:
```tsx
// Bad: State trong parent causes all children to re-render
function Parent() {
  const [input, setInput] = useState('');
  return (
    <>
      <Input value={input} onChange={setInput} />
      <ExpensiveList /> {/* Re-renders on every input! */}
    </>
  );
}

// Good: Isolate state
function Parent() {
  return (
    <>
      <SearchInput /> {/* Has own state */}
      <ExpensiveList />
    </>
  );
}
```

**5. Children pattern**:
```tsx
function Layout({ children }) {
  const [state, setState] = useState();
  return <div>{children}</div>; // children không re-render khi state changes
}
```

**Measure first**: Dùng React DevTools Profiler trước khi optimize

**Khi dùng Context**:
- Theme (dark/light mode)
- User authentication state
- Locale/language preferences
- Global UI state (modals, toasts)
- Dependency injection (services, configs)

**Tạo Context**:
```tsx
const ThemeContext = createContext<Theme | null>(null);

export function ThemeProvider({ children }) {
  const [theme, setTheme] = useState<Theme>('light');
  return (
    <ThemeContext.Provider value={{ theme, setTheme }}>
      {children}
    </ThemeContext.Provider>
  );
}

export function useTheme() {
  const context = useContext(ThemeContext);
  if (!context) throw new Error('useTheme must be within ThemeProvider');
  return context;
}
```

**Performance Pitfalls**:

1. **All consumers re-render khi value changes**:
```tsx
// Bad: New object on every render
<Context.Provider value={{ user, settings }}>

// Good: Memoize value
const value = useMemo(() => ({ user, settings }), [user, settings]);
<Context.Provider value={value}>
```

2. **Tách contexts**:
```tsx
// Bad: Một context cho mọi thứ
<AppContext.Provider value={{ user, theme, settings }}>

// Good: Separate concerns
<UserContext.Provider value={user}>
  <ThemeContext.Provider value={theme}>
```

**Khi KHÔNG dùng Context**:
- Frequently changing values (form inputs)
- Complex state logic → Redux, Zustand
- Server state → TanStack Query, SWR

**Alternatives**:
- **Zustand**: Simple, minimal boilerplate
- **Jotai**: Atomic state management
- **Redux Toolkit**: Complex apps với DevTools
- **TanStack Query**: Server state

**Controlled Components**:
- React state là "single source of truth"
- Value được control bởi React
- Mọi change đi qua onChange handler

```tsx
function ControlledForm() {
  const [email, setEmail] = useState('');
  return (
    <input
      value={email}
      onChange={(e) => setEmail(e.target.value)}
    />
  );
}
```

**Uncontrolled Components**:
- DOM là source of truth
- Dùng refs để access values
- Ít re-renders

```tsx
function UncontrolledForm() {
  const inputRef = useRef<HTMLInputElement>(null);
  const handleSubmit = () => {
    console.log(inputRef.current?.value);
  };
  return <input ref={inputRef} defaultValue="" />;
}
```

**So sánh**:
| Feature | Controlled | Uncontrolled |
|---------|------------|---------------|
| Validation | Real-time | On submit |
| Performance | More re-renders | Fewer re-renders |
| Testing | Easier | Harder |
| Form state | In React | In DOM |

**Khi dùng Controlled**:
- Real-time validation
- Conditional rendering based on input
- Format/mask input values
- Complex form logic

**Khi dùng Uncontrolled**:
- File inputs (`<input type="file">`)
- Simple forms không cần real-time validation
- Performance-critical với many inputs
- Third-party DOM libraries

**React Hook Form** — Best of both:
```tsx
const { register, handleSubmit } = useForm();
return (
  <form onSubmit={handleSubmit(onSubmit)}>
    <input {...register('email')} />
  </form>
);
// Uncontrolled internally, but provides controlled-like API
```

**Custom Hook là gì?**
- Function bắt đầu với `use`
- Có thể gọi các hooks khác
- Encapsulate reusable stateful logic
- Mỗi component dùng hook có state riêng

**Ví dụ cơ bản**:
```tsx
function useToggle(initial = false) {
  const [value, setValue] = useState(initial);
  const toggle = useCallback(() => setValue(v => !v), []);
  const setTrue = useCallback(() => setValue(true), []);
  const setFalse = useCallback(() => setValue(false), []);
  return { value, toggle, setTrue, setFalse };
}

// Usage
const { value: isOpen, toggle } = useToggle();
```

**Data fetching hook**:
```tsx
function useFetch<T>(url: string) {
  const [data, setData] = useState<T | null>(null);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);
  const [error, setError] = useState<Error | null>(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    const controller = new AbortController();
    fetch(url, { signal: controller.signal })
      .then(res => res.json())
      .then(setData)
      .catch(setError)
      .finally(() => setLoading(false));
    return () => controller.abort();
  }, [url]);

  return { data, loading, error };
}
```

**Rules of Hooks**:
1. Chỉ gọi hooks ở top level (không trong loops, conditions)
2. Chỉ gọi từ React functions (components hoặc custom hooks)
3. Tên phải bắt đầu với `use`

**Patterns**:
- **Return object**: Flexible destructuring
- **Return tuple**: Simple, like useState
- **Composition**: Hook gọi hooks khác

**Testing**:
```tsx
import { renderHook, act } from '@testing-library/react';

test('useToggle', () => {
  const { result } = renderHook(() => useToggle());
  expect(result.current.value).toBe(false);
  act(() => result.current.toggle());
  expect(result.current.value).toBe(true);
});
```

**Error Boundary là gì?**
- Class component catch JavaScript errors trong child component tree
- Display fallback UI thay vì crash whole app
- Chỉ class components có thể là error boundaries (hiện tại)

**Implementation**:
```tsx
class ErrorBoundary extends React.Component<Props, State> {
  state = { hasError: false, error: null };

  static getDerivedStateFromError(error: Error) {
    return { hasError: true, error };
  }

  componentDidCatch(error: Error, info: ErrorInfo) {
    // Log to error reporting service
    logErrorToService(error, info.componentStack);
  }

  render() {
    if (this.state.hasError) {
      return this.props.fallback || <h1>Something went wrong.</h1>;
    }
    return this.props.children;
  }
}
```

**Không catch được**:
- Event handlers (dùng try/catch)
- Async code (promises, setTimeout)
- Server-side rendering
- Errors trong boundary itself

**Production patterns**:

1. **Multiple boundaries** at different levels:
```tsx
<AppErrorBoundary>
  <Header />
  <PageErrorBoundary>
    <MainContent />
  </PageErrorBoundary>
  <Footer />
</AppErrorBoundary>
```

2. **Reset on navigation**:
```tsx
function PageErrorBoundary({ children }) {
  const location = useLocation();
  return (
    <ErrorBoundary key={location.pathname}>
      {children}
    </ErrorBoundary>
  );
}
```

3. **react-error-boundary package**:
```tsx
import { ErrorBoundary } from 'react-error-boundary';

<ErrorBoundary
  fallbackRender={({ error, resetErrorBoundary }) => (
    <div>
      <p>{error.message}</p>
      <button onClick={resetErrorBoundary}>Try again</button>
    </div>
  )}
  onReset={() => queryClient.clear()}
>
```

**File Conventions**:

**page.tsx** — Unique UI cho route:
```tsx
// app/dashboard/page.tsx → /dashboard
export default function DashboardPage() {
  return <h1>Dashboard</h1>;
}
```

**layout.tsx** — Shared UI cho segment và children:
```tsx
// app/dashboard/layout.tsx
export default function DashboardLayout({ children }) {
  return (
    <div>
      <Sidebar />
      <main>{children}</main>
    </div>
  );
}
// Layout persists across page navigations
```

**loading.tsx** — Loading UI với Suspense:
```tsx
// app/dashboard/loading.tsx
export default function Loading() {
  return <Skeleton />;
}
// Automatically wrapped in Suspense
```

**error.tsx** — Error UI:
```tsx
'use client';
export default function Error({ error, reset }) {
  return (
    <div>
      <h2>Something went wrong!</h2>
      <button onClick={reset}>Try again</button>
    </div>
  );
}
// Must be client component
```

**not-found.tsx** — 404 UI:
```tsx
// app/not-found.tsx hoặc app/[...slug]/not-found.tsx
export default function NotFound() {
  return <h1>Page not found</h1>;
}
// Triggered by notFound() function
```

**template.tsx** — Like layout but re-mounts:
```tsx
// Useful for enter/exit animations
export default function Template({ children }) {
  return <motion.div initial={{ opacity: 0 }}>{children}</motion.div>;
}
```

**Hierarchy**:
```
layout.tsx
  template.tsx
    error.tsx
      loading.tsx
        page.tsx / not-found.tsx
```

**Middleware Auth** — Protect routes:
```tsx
// middleware.ts
import { NextResponse } from 'next/server';

export function middleware(request: NextRequest) {
  const token = request.cookies.get('session')?.value;

  if (!token && request.nextUrl.pathname.startsWith('/dashboard')) {
    return NextResponse.redirect(new URL('/login', request.url));
  }

  return NextResponse.next();
}

export const config = {
  matcher: ['/dashboard/:path*', '/api/:path*']
};
```

**Server Component Auth**:
```tsx
// lib/auth.ts
import { cookies } from 'next/headers';

export async function getSession() {
  const sessionToken = (await cookies()).get('session')?.value;
  if (!sessionToken) return null;
  return await validateSession(sessionToken);
}

// app/dashboard/page.tsx
export default async function DashboardPage() {
  const session = await getSession();
  if (!session) redirect('/login');

  return <Dashboard user={session.user} />;
}
```

**Session Management Options**:

1. **JWT in cookies**:
```tsx
const token = jwt.sign({ userId: user.id }, SECRET);
cookies().set('session', token, {
  httpOnly: true,
  secure: process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production',
  sameSite: 'lax',
  maxAge: 60 * 60 * 24 * 7 // 1 week
});
```

2. **Database sessions**:
```tsx
const sessionId = crypto.randomUUID();
await db.sessions.create({ id: sessionId, userId: user.id });
cookies().set('session', sessionId, { ... });
```

**NextAuth.js / Auth.js**:
```tsx
import NextAuth from 'next-auth';
import GitHub from 'next-auth/providers/github';

export const { auth, signIn, signOut } = NextAuth({
  providers: [GitHub],
});
```

**Best Practices**:
- HttpOnly cookies cho tokens
- CSRF protection
- Session rotation
- Secure flag in production

**Server Components fetch** — Direct database/API access:
```tsx
// app/posts/page.tsx
async function getPosts() {
  const res = await fetch('https://api.example.com/posts');
  return res.json();
}

export default async function PostsPage() {
  const posts = await getPosts();
  return <PostList posts={posts} />;
}
```

**Caching Defaults (Next.js 15)**:
- `fetch()` không cache by default (changed from 14)
- Opt-in caching với options

**Caching options**:
```tsx
// Cache indefinitely (static)
fetch(url, { cache: 'force-cache' });

// No cache (dynamic)
fetch(url, { cache: 'no-store' });

// Revalidate after N seconds
fetch(url, { next: { revalidate: 60 } });

// Revalidate on demand với tags
fetch(url, { next: { tags: ['posts'] } });
```

**Revalidation Strategies**:

1. **Time-based** (ISR):
```tsx
export const revalidate = 3600; // Revalidate every hour
```

2. **On-demand** với tags:
```tsx
// Fetch với tag
fetch(url, { next: { tags: ['posts'] } });

// Revalidate trong Server Action
import { revalidateTag } from 'next/cache';
await revalidateTag('posts');
```

3. **Path-based**:
```tsx
import { revalidatePath } from 'next/cache';
revalidatePath('/posts');
```

**Direct database access**:
```tsx
import { db } from '@/lib/db';

export default async function UsersPage() {
  // Direct query, no fetch needed
  const users = await db.user.findMany();
  return <UserList users={users} />;
}
```

**Parallel fetching**:
```tsx
const [posts, users] = await Promise.all([
  getPosts(),
  getUsers()
]);
```

**Event Loop Phases** (theo thứ tự):

1. **Timers**: `setTimeout`, `setInterval` callbacks
2. **Pending callbacks**: I/O callbacks deferred từ previous iteration
3. **Idle, prepare**: Internal use
4. **Poll**: Retrieve new I/O events, execute I/O callbacks
5. **Check**: `setImmediate` callbacks
6. **Close callbacks**: `socket.on('close')`

**Giữa mỗi phase**: Microtasks (Promises, `process.nextTick`) được drain

**`process.nextTick` vs `setImmediate`**:
```js
setImmediate(() => console.log('setImmediate'));
process.nextTick(() => console.log('nextTick'));
// Output: nextTick, setImmediate
// nextTick chạy trước bất kỳ I/O hoặc timers nào
```

**setTimeout vs setImmediate** (tricky case):
```js
setTimeout(() => console.log('timeout'), 0);
setImmediate(() => console.log('immediate'));
// Output: Không xác định! Phụ thuộc vào process performance
```

**Trong I/O callback** (predictable):
```js
fs.readFile('file.txt', () => {
  setTimeout(() => console.log('timeout'), 0);
  setImmediate(() => console.log('immediate'));
});
// Output: immediate, timeout
// Vì check phase đến sau poll phase
```

**Microtask queue**:
```js
Promise.resolve().then(() => console.log('promise'));
process.nextTick(() => console.log('nextTick'));
// Output: nextTick, promise
// nextTick có priority cao hơn Promises
```

**Starvation risk**:
```js
function recursiveNextTick() {
  process.nextTick(recursiveNextTick);
}
recursiveNextTick();
// I/O sẽ bị starved! Event loop stuck trong nextTick queue
```

**EventEmitter Basics**:
```js
const EventEmitter = require('events');

class MyEmitter extends EventEmitter {}
const emitter = new MyEmitter();

// Listen
emitter.on('event', (data) => console.log(data));

// Emit
emitter.emit('event', { message: 'Hello' });

// Once
emitter.once('init', () => console.log('Initialized'));
```

**Error Handling** — Critical:
```js
// Unhandled 'error' event crashes process!
emitter.emit('error', new Error('Oops'));
// Error: Oops (unhandled)

// Always add error handler
emitter.on('error', (err) => {
  console.error('Handled:', err.message);
});
```

**Memory Leak Prevention**:

1. **Remove listeners**:
```js
function handler(data) { ... }
emitter.on('event', handler);
// Later
emitter.off('event', handler); // or removeListener
```

2. **Listener limit warning**:
```js
emitter.setMaxListeners(20); // Default is 10
// Warning: Possible EventEmitter memory leak detected
```

3. **Use once for one-time events**:
```js
emitter.once('ready', () => {
  // Automatically removed after firing
});
```

**AbortSignal pattern** (modern):
```js
const controller = new AbortController();
emitter.on('event', handler, { signal: controller.signal });
// Later
controller.abort(); // Removes the listener
```

**Typed EventEmitter** (TypeScript):
```ts
interface Events {
  data: [Buffer];
  error: [Error];
  end: [];
}

class TypedEmitter extends EventEmitter {
  emit<K extends keyof Events>(event: K, ...args: Events[K]): boolean {
    return super.emit(event, ...args);
  }
  on<K extends keyof Events>(event: K, listener: (...args: Events[K]) => void) {
    return super.on(event, listener);
  }
}
```

**Passport Strategy Setup**:
```ts
// auth/strategies/local.strategy.ts
@Injectable()
export class LocalStrategy extends PassportStrategy(Strategy) {
  constructor(private authService: AuthService) {
    super({ usernameField: 'email' });
  }

  async validate(email: string, password: string): Promise<User> {
    const user = await this.authService.validateUser(email, password);
    if (!user) throw new UnauthorizedException();
    return user;
  }
}
```

**Session-based Auth**:
```ts
// main.ts
import session from 'express-session';
import passport from 'passport';

app.use(session({
  secret: process.env.SESSION_SECRET,
  resave: false,
  saveUninitialized: false,
  cookie: { maxAge: 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000 }
}));
app.use(passport.initialize());
app.use(passport.session());

// Serializer
@Injectable()
